/power_stage.ppmdata exch def
/power_stage.ppm <<
  /ImageType 1 /Width 800 /Height 957 /BitsPerComponent 8
  /MultipleDataSources false
  /Decode [0 1 0 1 0 1]
  /ImageMatrix [1 0 0 -1 400 478]
  /DataSource power_stage.ppmdata >> def


%%EndSetup

%%Page: power_stage 1
%%PageOrientation: Portrait
%%PageBoundingBox: 0 0 612 792
/pgsave save def bop
0.5821 inchscale
2.6000 setlinewidth 1257 2112 translate

(power_stage) {/Helvetica-Bold cf} 2 16 0.000 1.500 -928 992 label
1 1.000 -928 960 1152 960 2 polygon
(Power pMOS switch in a waffle configuration layout for IHP sg13cmos5l) 
{/Helvetica cf} 2 16 0.000 1.000 -928 896 label
(Description:) {/Helvetica-Oblique cf} 2 16 0.000 1.000 -928 800 label
(Circuit layout of power_stage) {/Helvetica-Oblique cf} 2 16 0.000 1.000 496 
816 label
(number of devices.) {CR} 
(pMOS layout in a waffle configuration with a parameterized) {CR} 
(This repository contains a generation script for creating a power) 
{/Helvetica cf} 6 28 0.000 1.000 -928 736 label
/power_stage.ppm 1.000 0.000 816 304 graphic
(\32720 with digital control.) {/HelveticaISO cf} 
(layout of a power switch of size 20) {CR} 
(In addition to the device generation script, there is a completed) 
{/Helvetica cf} 6 28 0.000 1.000 -928 560 label
(Device generator script:) {/Helvetica-Oblique cf} 2 16 0.000 1.000 -928 384 
label
(line, do:) {CR} ( layout tool.  From the magic command) {/Helvetica cf} 
(magic) {/Helvetica-Bold cf} (be used in the ) {CR} ( and is meant to) 
{/Helvetica cf} (pmos_waffle.tcl) {/Helvetica-Bold cf} 
(The device generator script is ) {/Helvetica cf} 14 28 0.000 1.000 -928 320 
label
(source ../scripts/pmos_waffle.tcl) {/Courier cf} 2 16 0.000 1.000 -832 112 
label
(.) {/HelveticaISO cf} (magic/pmos_waffle_20.mag) {/Helvetica-BoldISO cf} 
(can also be found as a layout in ) {CR} (\32720 array, which) 
{/HelveticaISO cf} (which will generate the default device with a 20) 
{/Helvetica cf} 10 28 0.000 1.000 -928 32 label
( prior to sourcing the script:) {/Helvetica cf} (waffle_size) {/Courier cf} 
{CR} (To create a device with a different array size, set the variable) 
{/Helvetica cf} 7 28 0.000 1.000 -928 -112 label
(source ../scripts/pmos_waffle.tcl) {CR} (set waffle_size 10) {/Courier cf} 4 
28 0.000 1.000 -832 -240 label
(vertical and horizontal orientations.) {CR} 
(between devices in the array.  Devices are placed in a checkerboard pattern with transistors on each side in both) 
{CR} (\265m, allowing for a 5\265m pitch) {/HelveticaISO cf} 
(The pFET device made is a 3.3V \(thick oxide\) device.  Each transistor has width 4.36) 
{/Helvetica cf} 8 28 0.000 1.000 -928 -384 label
(\265m.) {/HelveticaISO cf} 
(20, there are 760 transistors, for a total transistor width of 3313.6) {CR} 
( of) {/Helvetica cf} (waffle_size) {/Courier cf} 
(The total number of transistors is \(2 * waffle_size * \(waffle_size - 1\)\).  For example, for the default ) 
{/Helvetica cf} 10 28 0.000 1.000 -928 -544 label
